00:09:33.370 --> 00:09:46.180
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:09:46.180 --> 00:09:48.360
- Even though formally
speaking earlier work

00:09:48.360 --> 00:09:50.640
might be really different
from later work,

00:09:50.640 --> 00:09:54.120
but actually earlier work
serves as a commentary

00:09:54.120 --> 00:09:56.560
or interpretation of later work.

00:09:56.560 --> 00:10:02.280
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:10:02.280 --> 00:10:04.470
- I started off
learning printmaking,

00:10:04.470 --> 00:10:08.170
and I received my education in
the People's Republic of China.

00:10:08.170 --> 00:10:12.820
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:10:12.820 --> 00:10:15.480
- I wanted to briefly
first introduce this.

00:10:15.480 --> 00:10:18.800
This work is called a
five series of repetition.

00:10:18.800 --> 00:10:23.720
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:10:23.720 --> 00:10:28.590
- So what this word is I was
examining the repetitive nature

00:10:28.590 --> 00:10:30.620
of print-making.

00:10:30.620 --> 00:10:43.370
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:10:43.370 --> 00:10:46.990
- So I've always been, sort of,
examining why does print-making

00:10:46.990 --> 00:10:50.890
exist as an art form and
alongside things like oil

00:10:50.890 --> 00:10:53.810
painting and other
forms of painting.

00:10:53.810 --> 00:11:12.340
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:11:12.340 --> 00:11:15.370
- So it's the same block, but
on the left this was before

00:11:15.370 --> 00:11:17.010
anything had been carved .

00:11:17.010 --> 00:11:19.630
And then the middle it's when
a few things had been carved.

00:11:19.630 --> 00:11:21.910
And then later more
things have been carved.

00:11:21.910 --> 00:11:23.500
And this was-- this
is the same block,

00:11:23.500 --> 00:11:27.217
but it was all printed in a
series on a piece of paper.

00:11:31.040 --> 00:11:35.080
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:11:35.080 --> 00:11:37.200
- And I continue to carve
and continue to print.

00:11:37.200 --> 00:11:39.180
It's actually all
just one block.

00:11:39.180 --> 00:11:44.260
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:11:44.260 --> 00:11:46.620
- Though in normal conception,
the one on the left

00:11:46.620 --> 00:11:49.980
should be what we consider
a completed print.

00:11:49.980 --> 00:11:51.690
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:11:51.690 --> 00:11:53.850
- But I continue to carve.

00:11:53.850 --> 00:11:55.860
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:11:55.860 --> 00:11:58.592
- And then the images
start to disappear.

00:11:58.592 --> 00:12:03.630
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:12:03.630 --> 00:12:06.630
- And so in the end it becomes
a work where there's nothing

00:12:06.630 --> 00:12:07.830
there and just white.

00:12:07.830 --> 00:12:11.710
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:12:11.710 --> 00:12:13.380
- So it's a process
of transforming

00:12:13.380 --> 00:12:17.330
from a black nothingness
to a white nothingness.

00:12:17.330 --> 00:12:24.530
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:12:24.530 --> 00:12:27.410
- So this type of
plurality is something

00:12:27.410 --> 00:12:29.746
that I think has
a special power.

00:12:29.746 --> 00:12:38.330
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:12:38.330 --> 00:12:41.040
- It's the same reason why the
New York Times, for example,

00:12:41.040 --> 00:12:44.480
has such power, because
it has this plurality.

00:12:44.480 --> 00:12:46.520
It has this series
repetitive nature.

00:12:46.520 --> 00:12:49.280
That's why it can be
distributed around the world.

00:12:49.280 --> 00:13:01.100
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:13:01.100 --> 00:13:03.790
- That's why cell phones,
for example, today--

00:13:03.790 --> 00:13:05.600
cell phone interfaces
have such power,

00:13:05.600 --> 00:13:08.355
because they can be
endlessly repeated.

00:13:08.355 --> 00:13:17.220
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:13:17.220 --> 00:13:20.900
- So contemporary society has
a particular characteristic,

00:13:20.900 --> 00:13:24.170
which is that it takes us
into this space where things

00:13:24.170 --> 00:13:26.210
are endlessly reproduced.

00:13:26.210 --> 00:13:33.020
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:13:33.020 --> 00:13:34.760
- A lot of Avant
Garde disciplines

00:13:34.760 --> 00:13:38.570
when they go into this
Avant Garde sort of area,

00:13:38.570 --> 00:13:42.730
it all has to do with repetitive
nature, including biology.

00:13:42.730 --> 00:13:47.960
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:13:47.960 --> 00:13:51.980
- This is a Book of the
Sky, which dean has already

00:13:51.980 --> 00:13:52.580
introduced.

00:13:52.580 --> 00:14:00.350
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:14:00.350 --> 00:14:02.510
- This was an
installation, but it was

00:14:02.510 --> 00:14:05.210
composed of many, many words.

00:14:05.210 --> 00:14:11.210
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:14:11.210 --> 00:14:13.350
- These words look a lot
like Chinese characters,

00:14:13.350 --> 00:14:16.760
but there isn't a single one of
them that can be actually read.

00:14:16.760 --> 00:14:21.680
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:14:21.680 --> 00:14:23.760
- And I was very
assiduous about this,

00:14:23.760 --> 00:14:27.590
so every single character
was hand-carved and printed.

00:14:27.590 --> 00:14:35.660
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:14:35.660 --> 00:14:38.480
- Because I wanted this
book to have a lot of,

00:14:38.480 --> 00:14:41.120
sort of, gravitas so that
people, when they read it,

00:14:41.120 --> 00:14:44.120
they wouldn't be able to
believe that all this effort

00:14:44.120 --> 00:14:46.730
and it becomes a book
that you can't read.

00:14:46.730 --> 00:14:55.380
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:14:55.380 --> 00:14:57.560
- So in 1990, I came
to the United States

00:14:57.560 --> 00:15:02.530
and my work then was all
slightly smaller installations.

00:15:02.530 --> 00:15:08.740
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:15:08.740 --> 00:15:10.830
- But then I realized
wherever you live

00:15:10.830 --> 00:15:15.230
and wherever a problem exists
that there art exists to.

00:15:15.230 --> 00:15:21.410
- [SPEAKING CHINESE]

00:15:21.410 --> 00:15:23.240
- So back then a
lot of my work had

00:15:23.240 --> 00:15:25.490
to do with language and
culture and the clash

00:15:25.490 --> 00:15:27.240
